\c 3
\s1 Jesus tells Nicodemus about the need to be reborn
\p
\v 1 One night a Jewish leader named Nicodemus who was a member of the Pharisee party
\v 2 came to Jesus and said, “Teacher, we know that God has sent you as a teacher¦64469, because no one could do these kinds of miracles if God wasn't with him.”
\p
\v 3 Jesus responded, “I'll tell you frankly that no one can enter God's kingdom¦64511 unless he is reborn.”
\p
\v 4 Nicodemus questioned, “How could an adult be reborn? A person can't just return to their mother's womb and¦64538 then get born again!”
\p
\v 5 And Jesus continued, “Honestly, I'm telling you: unless a person is born from both water¦64554 \em and\em* the spirit, they can't enter God's kingdom.
\v 6 Someone that's born from a body is flesh, but someone that's born from God's spirit is spiritual.
\v 7 So you shouldn't be surprised that I told you that everyone needs to be reborn.
\v 8 The wind blows wherever it wants, and you hear its sound but you can't actually see where it's coming from and where it's going. So too with everyone born from God's spirit.”
\p
\v 9 Nicodemus replied, “How can all this even happen?”
\p
\v 10 And Jesus answered, “You're a Jewish teacher¦64645 and yet you¦64651 don't know all this?
\v 11 It's true that we just teach what we know, and explain what we've seen¦64663 ourselves, but you people aren't accepting our testimony.
\v 12 If I tell you all earthly things and you don't believe them, how will you ever believe if I explain \em heavenly\em* things?
\v 13 None of you have gone up into heaven, except that I¦64710, mankind's child, have come down from heaven.
\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 3:14: \xt Num 21:9.\x*“Just like Moses lifted up that \add bronze\add* snake \add on a pole\add* in the wilderness, it's necessary for mankind's child to be lifted up,\f + \fr 3:14 \ft lifted up / exalted: See https://bibleDifferences.net/2019/04/25/156-exulted\f*
