\v 4 Whenever he moves the sheep, he goes in front and the sheep follow him because they recognise his voice.
\v 5 They would never follow¦72491 a stranger because they wouldn't know his voice, in fact they'd run away from him.
\p
\v 6 Jesus told them this illustration, but none of those who heard it knew¦72517 what it meant.
\s1 Jesus is the good shepherd
\p
\v 7 So Jesus continued, “Honestly I will tell you¦72535 that \em I am\em* the entrance for the sheep¦72545.
\v 8 The ones who came¦72548 before me are thieves and¦72554 robbers, but¦72556 the sheep¦72563 didn't listen to them.
\v 9 \em I am\em* the entrance. Anyone who comes in via me will be saved, and will be able to go in and out and find pasture.
\v 10 The thief only comes to steal and kill and destroy, but I came¦72600 so that they could live, and live a full life¦72602.
