\v 11 “\em I am\em* the good shepherd—the good shepherd gives his own life¦72621 for the sheep¦72627.\f + \fr 10:11 \ft See http://bibleandtech.blogspot.com/2021/04/john-1011-18-translations-and-notes-rcl.html\f*
\v 12 The paid worker is not even the shepherd, because the sheep aren't his own and if he sees a wolf coming he just abandons the sheep and takes off and the wolf scatters the sheep and snatches some—
\v 13 that's because he's just a worker and doesn't really care about the sheep¦72680.
\v 14 \em I am\em* the good¦72686 shepherd¦72684 and I know my \add sheep\add* and they know me,
\v 15 \x + \xo 10:15: \xt Mat 11:27; Luk 10:22.\x*just like the father knows me and I know the father—in fact I will give my life for the sheep.
\v 16 I also have other sheep which are not in this field¦72735 and it's appropriate for me to bring those other sheep also, then they'll be hearing my voice because there'll be just one flock with one shepherd.
\p
\v 17 The father¦72760 loves me because I am laying down my life¦72767 so that I can receive it¦72772 again.
\v 18 No one is taking it from me, but I'm laying it down myself. I have authority to lay it down, and also authority to receive it back again because I received this command from my father¦72807.”
\p
\v 19 The Jewish religious leaders were again divided about Jesus' teaching
\v 20 with many of them saying, “He's got a demon,” and, “He's stark raving mad—why are you¦72835 all even listening to him!”
\p
\v 21 But others were saying, “He doesn't sound like he's demon-possessed. And how could a demon make a blind man see?”
\s1 The Jewish leaders won't accept Jesus' teaching
\p
\v 22 By then it was winter and the time for the Jewish Feast of Dedication in Jerusalem.
\v 23 Jesus was walking¦72872 in the temple in an area known as Solomon's Porch
\v 24 when he was surrounded by the Jewish religious leaders and interrogated, “How long do you plan to keep us in suspense for? If you are the messiah, tell us clearly.”
\p
\v 25 So Jesus answered, “I already told you all but you didn't believe me. The miracles that I do with the authority of my father¦72934 testify about me,
\v 26 but you don't believe them either because you aren't part of my flock.
\v 27 My sheep¦72962 listen to my voice, and I know them and they¦72975 follow after me.
\v 28 I give them life¦72982 which will never end so they¦72987 won't ever be destroyed, and no one will be able to snatch them away from me.
\v 29 My father is the one who gave them to me, and he's more powerful than any other, so no one can snatch them away from him.
\v 30 The father¦73032 and¦73030 I are one.”
\p
\v 31 Again the Jewish leaders picked up rocks to throw at him to kill him.
\v 32 But Jesus asked, “I showed you all many miracles from my father¦73060. Which miracle do you want to kill me for?”
\p
\v 33 \x + \xo 10:33: \xt Lev 24:16.\x*They answered, “It's not for any \em good\em* deed that we think you deserve to die, but because you, a human, dishonour God by claiming to be him.”
\p
\v 34 \x + \xo 10:34: \xt Psa 82:6.\x*Jesus answered, “Isn't it written in your scriptures that God said, ‘You all are gods’?”
\v 35 Now the scriptures can't be wrong, and¦73132 if the ones who heard teaching from God were called gods,
\v 36 why are you¦73147 telling the one that the father¦73140 blessed and¦73142 sent¦73143 out into the world that I am insulting God because I said¦73152 that I'm God's son?
\v 37 If I'm not doing my father's work, then you don't need to believe that he sent me,
\v 38 but if I am doing his work, even if you don't believe that he sent me, at least believe in what I do so that you all can know that the father is in me and I'm in the father.”
\p
\v 39 That was enough that they tried yet again to arrest him, but he was able to get away from their influence.
\p
\v 40 \x + \xo 10:40: \xt Jn 1:28.\x*Then Jesus crossed the Jordan river to the place¦73227 where John had immersed the people, and he stayed there.
\v 41 Many people visited him there, and they were saying that even though John had never done even one miracle, on the other hand, everything that he had said about Jesus was true,
