\p
\v 27 Martha replied, “Yes, master, I do believe that you¦73774 are the messiah, God's son, the one sent into this world.”
\s1 Jesus weeps with his close friends
\p
\v 28 After saying this, Martha went¦73792 and quietly called her sister¦73797 Mary, “The teacher¦73806 is on his way and he wants to see you.”
\v 29 So Mary quickly¦73818 stood up and¦73819 went to find him.
\v 30 At that stage, Jesus hadn't yet come¦73828 into the village proper, but¦73835 was still at the edge where Martha had met him.
\v 31 The Judean people who'd been sitting with Mary in sympathy there in the house¦73856, when they saw her get up quickly¦73865 and go out, they assumed that she was going¦73878 to the cemetary to weep there.
\p
\v 32 But when Mary found Jesus, she¦73891 knelt at his feet¦73906 and said, “Master, if you'd been here my brother¦73921 wouldn't have died.”
\p
\v 33 Now when Jesus saw¦73926 her weeping there, along with the others that had followed also weeping, he himself was quite affected and groaned inside,
\v 34 but he just asked, “Where has he been laid?”
\p “Master, come and see,” they replied.
\p
