\p
\v 37 But some of them mocked, “This is the man who could make a blind man see again. How come he wasn't able to stop this man from dying!”
\s1 Jesus calls Lazarus back to life
\p
\v 38 So Jesus who was still holding back sobs, went to the cemetary. Lazarus' body had been placed in a cave with a stone¦74021 blocking it,
\v 39 and Jesus instructed them to take away the stone¦74030.
\p Martha (the sister¦74036 of the dead man) spoke up, “Master, the stink will be bad because it's already been four days.”
\p
\v 40 But Jesus responded, “Didn't I tell you that if you would believe, then you would see God's power?”
\v 41 So they took¦74064 the stone¦74068 away and Jesus looked upwards and said, “Father, I thank you that you listen to me.
