\v 43 After saying that, he¦74116 shouted, “Lazarus¦74119, come¦74121 out!”
\v 44 Then the man who had died¦74127 \add slowly\add* shuffled out—still with linen strips wrapped around his hands¦74136 and his feet¦74131, and a cloth wrapped around his face.
\s1 The leaders create a plan to execute Jesus
\r (Mat. 26:1-5; Mrk. 14:1-2; Luk. 22:1-2)
\p
\v 45 Because of that, many of the Judeans believed that Jesus was from God after having followed Mary and¦74171 seeing what Jesus did.
\v 46 But others went¦74187 and¦74192 told the Pharisee party what Jesus had done.
\v 47 So the chief priests¦74206 and the Pharisee party called a formal meeting and asked, “What should we¦74215 do because this man is doing many miracles.
\v 48 If we allow him to continue like this, all the crowds will be believing he's the messiah, and then the Romans will come and destroy both our temple and our governance.”
\p
\v 49 But one of them, Caiaphas who was chief priest¦74261 that year, spoke up, “You don't know anything.
