\v 51 He didn't say this from his own thinking, but being chief priest¦74300 that year, he was announcing God's message that Jesus was going¦74310 to die for the nation¦74317,
\v 52 and not only for this nation¦74322, but¦74324 for all of God's children¦74328 scattered around the world to become united.
\p
\v 53 As a result, from that day¦74343 on they decided that Jesus needed to be executed.
\v 54 Because of that, Jesus no longer walked around Judea in public, but¦74360 went¦74361 out to the town of Ephraim out in the wilderness and¦74374 stayed there with his followers.
\p
\v 55 At that time, the Jewish Passover celebrations were approaching, and¦74392 many people from the regions went¦74393 to Jerusalem ahead of the celebrations to purify themselves.
\v 56 They were looking out for Jesus and as they stood around in the temple, asked each other, “What do you think? Surely he won't come¦74433 to the celebrations.”
\v 57 The chief priests¦74442 and the Pharisee party had already announced that if anyone knew where Jesus was, they must inform them so that they could arrest him.
\c 12
