\p Jesus¦75266 said these things¦75263 and then after leaving them, he was hidden from them.
\s1 Many people refuse to stand for Jesus
\p
\v 37 Even though Jesus had done so many miracles in front of the people, they¦75283 didn't believe that he was the messiah.
\v 38 \x + \xo 12:38: \xt Isa 53:1 (LXX).\x*This fulfilled what the prophet Isaiah wrote,
\q1 “Master, who believed our report?
\q1 And who was the master's power revealed to?”
\p
\v 39 Because of this, they¦75311 weren't able to believe, and again as Isaiah¦75319 wrote,
\q1
\v 40 \x + \xo 12:40: \xt Isa 6:10 (LXX).\x*“He has blinded their eyes and maimed their emotions,
\q1 so that they can't see with their eyes and understand with their minds,
\q2 or they might be turned and then I would heal them.”
