\p
\v 28 Then they led Jesus out from Caiaphas and towards the residence of the governor. It was now the early hours of the morning and as Jews, they didn't enter the residence of the Roman governor so they wouldn't become defiled and thus unable to eat the Passover meal.
\v 29 So Governor Pilate came¦79672 outside to them and¦79682 asked, “What charge are you¦79687 all bringing against this man¦79690?”
