\v 20 Many Jews read this title because the place¦80444 where Jesus was executed was near the city¦80446, and it had been written in Hebrew, Latin, and Greek.
\v 21 But the chief priests¦80466 of the Jews complained to Pilate, “Don't write ‘The king of the Jews’, but rather ‘The one who said he was king of the Jews’.”
\p
\v 22 However Pilate answered, “What I've written, I've written.”
\p
